WEBVTT

00:00.022 --> 00:01.405
Previously on <i>Suits...</i>

00:01.430 --> 00:03.854
You're guilty of bribing
a foreign government

00:03.855 --> 00:05.106
to get your pipeline.

00:05.157 --> 00:07.208
Guilty as charged.

00:07.275 --> 00:08.555
You think
you're not replaceable?

00:08.577 --> 00:10.161
I've been doing this
before I met you,

00:10.245 --> 00:13.531
and I'll be doing it long after
I've forgotten all about you.

00:13.615 --> 00:14.665
Please don't do this.

00:14.750 --> 00:17.034
Your beloved associates
are mine.

00:17.119 --> 00:19.670
What you want is
a long, drawn-out trial

00:19.755 --> 00:20.988
that puts our stock
in the toilet.

00:21.039 --> 00:22.123
I'm here to tell you

00:22.174 --> 00:23.624
he's recusing himself
from the case.

00:23.675 --> 00:25.492
So he appointed
a special prosecutor.

00:25.544 --> 00:28.546
I win, you back me
for managing partner.

00:28.630 --> 00:30.464
You want
to take down Jessica.

00:30.515 --> 00:32.216
Yes, I do.

00:35.137 --> 00:37.271
Holy shit.

00:37.338 --> 00:39.724
Was that a good "holy shit"
or a bad "holy shit"?

00:39.808 --> 00:42.009
Harvey, you just told me
that you're planning a coup.

00:42.060 --> 00:43.644
Give me a second
to figure that out.

00:43.695 --> 00:46.513
Not a coup.
It's a move.

00:46.565 --> 00:48.032
And when you're done
with your lecture--

00:48.116 --> 00:49.367
No.
No lecture.

00:49.451 --> 00:52.903
I just have one question.

00:52.988 --> 00:56.157
Do I get my own office?

00:56.208 --> 00:57.658
Harvey, if you want
to be managing partner

00:57.709 --> 00:59.076
and Darby
agreed to back you,

00:59.161 --> 01:00.628
then I'll follow you
to the ends of the earth.

01:00.695 --> 01:02.747
But before we start,
I want to make sure

01:02.831 --> 01:04.632
you're ready to do this
to Jessica.

01:04.699 --> 01:06.634
I am.

01:06.701 --> 01:10.971
Then let's go beat the shit
out of Cameron Dennis.

01:11.039 --> 01:12.473
I know you don't want
to see me.

01:12.540 --> 01:14.308
And yet--

01:14.375 --> 01:15.726
I just wanted
to let you know that I got

01:15.811 --> 01:18.045
a copy of the letter that
Jessica blackmailed me with,

01:18.096 --> 01:19.546
and I made it clear to her
that I would take it

01:19.598 --> 01:21.432
to the D.A.
if she ever threatened me,

01:21.516 --> 01:23.017
so what I did
will never happen again.

01:23.068 --> 01:25.552
Never should have happened
in the first place.

01:25.604 --> 01:26.720
Close the door
on your way out.

01:26.772 --> 01:29.723
Donna and I
have work to do.

01:34.729 --> 01:38.199
There's a harsh reality
I need to inform you of,

01:38.250 --> 01:40.668
and it's a bitter pill
to swallow.

01:40.735 --> 01:43.737
But the truth is,
a mistake was made.

01:43.789 --> 01:45.706
A fatal mistake.

01:45.757 --> 01:47.908
And as much
as I hate to admit it,

01:47.959 --> 01:51.679
our time together is done.

01:51.746 --> 01:54.348
No more work,

01:54.415 --> 01:56.517
no more laughter.

01:56.584 --> 01:58.803
Remember?

02:00.188 --> 02:01.188
No more mentorship

02:01.256 --> 02:05.142
and, um, no more anything.

02:05.227 --> 02:08.195
See, I reached too high,
and I fell.

02:08.263 --> 02:10.364
And my punishment is the end
of my tenure

02:10.431 --> 02:13.117
as head of the associates.

02:13.201 --> 02:15.986
So I would like to leave you

02:16.071 --> 02:18.489
with the immortal sentiment

02:18.573 --> 02:21.575
of Robin Williams.

02:21.626 --> 02:23.828
There have been
other associates before you.

02:23.912 --> 02:26.947
They believed they
were destined for great things,

02:26.998 --> 02:28.332
just like you.

02:28.416 --> 02:33.170
If you just listen,

02:33.255 --> 02:37.091
you can hear 'em whisper
their legacy to you.

02:37.142 --> 02:39.426
Carpe diem.

02:41.480 --> 02:44.181
Seize the day, people.

02:44.266 --> 02:47.268
Make your legal lives
extraordinary.

02:47.319 --> 02:49.520
Oh, Captain,
my Captain.

02:53.742 --> 02:55.159
There was a time
I would've been relieved

02:55.243 --> 02:58.412
to see that--
no more Louis.

02:58.479 --> 02:59.446
It's just wrong.

02:59.498 --> 03:01.148
This whole merger
is wrong.

03:01.199 --> 03:03.150
How'd it go with Harvey?

03:03.201 --> 03:04.201
It didn't.

03:04.286 --> 03:05.152
Did you tell him
about Jessica?

03:05.203 --> 03:07.755
Yeah.
He didn't care.

03:09.624 --> 03:10.791
What?

03:10.842 --> 03:13.093
I just wish I could give you
a hug right now,

03:13.161 --> 03:15.930
but I can't because we still
want to keep us quiet.

03:15.997 --> 03:17.998
Well, come on.
You can give me a hug.

03:18.049 --> 03:19.600
Something could've happened.

03:19.667 --> 03:22.520
Something bad,
like a...

03:22.604 --> 03:23.554
My dog could've died.

03:23.638 --> 03:25.189
Oh, you have a dog now?

03:25.273 --> 03:28.142
I was really close
to this dog.

03:28.193 --> 03:30.194
Well, the best way
to get over the death of a dog

03:30.278 --> 03:31.645
is to get a new one.
Mmmm.

03:31.696 --> 03:32.980
- No?
- No.

03:33.031 --> 03:34.348
I'm just--I'm just too upset.

03:34.399 --> 03:36.367
I'm--I don't know
if I'm ready

03:36.451 --> 03:38.903
for a new fake dog
right now.

03:38.987 --> 03:40.037
- Okay.
- Yeah.

03:40.121 --> 03:42.039
Just leave me
like this.

03:46.717 --> 03:49.836
How did it go?

03:52.840 --> 03:55.275
I don't know.
Awful.

03:55.342 --> 03:56.893
Probably the hardest thing
I ever had to do.

03:56.977 --> 03:58.194
Louis, we just merged,

03:58.279 --> 04:01.197
and I wish I could undo
you losing the associates,

04:01.282 --> 04:02.782
but I can't.

04:02.850 --> 04:04.234
What I can do

04:04.318 --> 04:06.653
is take
what you've been giving

04:06.704 --> 04:09.205
to so many for so long

04:09.290 --> 04:11.074
and have you channel it
into one.

04:11.158 --> 04:12.959
You mean...

04:13.026 --> 04:15.962
I want you to mentor
your own associate.

04:19.834 --> 04:21.334
Finally.

04:21.385 --> 04:25.371
The D'Artagnan to my Athos,
Porthos, and Aramis.

04:25.423 --> 04:27.590
All for one
and one for all.

04:27.675 --> 04:29.926
<i>En garde!</i>

04:30.010 --> 04:32.345
Sorry.

04:32.396 --> 04:35.398
Jessica, wait.

04:35.483 --> 04:37.317
I can have anyone?

04:37.384 --> 04:39.903
Louis, take your pick
of the litter.

04:44.325 --> 04:46.192
- Good morning, Ms. Paulsen.
- Spit it out.

04:46.243 --> 04:47.660
Is that any way to start
the day?

04:47.728 --> 04:49.112
You want something.

04:49.196 --> 04:50.363
I need the 411
on the breakup.

04:50.414 --> 04:52.415
- Are we in high school?
- Life is high school.

04:52.500 --> 04:53.566
And I need to know
if the prom king

04:53.617 --> 04:55.919
and his boy wonder
are still an item.

04:56.003 --> 04:57.203
What high school
did you go to?

04:57.237 --> 04:58.955
Donna,
it's a simple question.

04:59.039 --> 05:01.291
Did Mike and Harvey
<i>break up</i> break up,

05:01.375 --> 05:04.043
or did they take a time-out
and, like, say to each other,

05:04.095 --> 05:06.546
"hey, let's see other people
and make sure that we're sure."

05:06.597 --> 05:09.048
I see what's going on here.

05:09.100 --> 05:10.467
Jessica feels sorry
for you,

05:10.551 --> 05:11.885
so she's given you
your pick of the liter.

05:11.936 --> 05:13.252
And now you're sniffing
around here,

05:13.304 --> 05:15.271
trying to put the moves on Mike
behind Harvey's back.

05:15.356 --> 05:17.316
No, no, no, no, no, no, no.
I would never do that.

05:17.391 --> 05:19.476
No, that's why I'm here
to ask permission.

05:19.560 --> 05:20.927
So ask him.

05:20.978 --> 05:21.978
Well, I think
it might go better

05:22.062 --> 05:23.029
coming
from a different source.

05:23.096 --> 05:24.898
- You want me to ask him.
- Yeah.

05:24.949 --> 05:25.932
Would you please?
No.

05:25.983 --> 05:27.033
Why?

05:27.100 --> 05:28.034
Because it would be
so much more fun

05:28.101 --> 05:30.737
for me to listen to you
ask him.

05:30.788 --> 05:31.821
Well, let me
get this straight.

05:31.906 --> 05:33.490
You want my permission
to take Mike

05:33.574 --> 05:35.208
and force him to be
your associate.

05:35.275 --> 05:36.993
No, I would never force him
to do anything.

05:37.077 --> 05:38.161
It has to be consensual.

05:38.245 --> 05:41.447
Not like Sally Jones
and senior prom.

05:41.499 --> 05:43.416
Wait a second.
Did you just admit to a crime?

05:43.467 --> 05:45.752
No, a crime was committed
upon me.

05:45.803 --> 05:47.954
Okay, I don't want to,
but I have to.

05:48.005 --> 05:49.806
What crime?

05:49.890 --> 05:52.959
My mom felt bad for Sally,
so she forced me to take her.

05:53.010 --> 05:56.563
Well, what was so bad
about her?

05:56.630 --> 06:00.400
She had four nipples.

06:00.467 --> 06:02.569
Okay, if that date
was so bad,

06:02.636 --> 06:04.938
I mean,
how did you find that out?

06:04.989 --> 06:05.939
Okay, you know what,
Harvey,

06:05.990 --> 06:07.574
do I have your blessing
or not?

06:07.641 --> 06:09.108
Knock yourself out,
Louis.

06:09.160 --> 06:10.693
See, no, no, no,
no, no, no, no.

06:10.778 --> 06:12.745
You're just saying that because
you think he's gonna say no.

06:12.813 --> 06:15.615
- Oh, I know he'll say no.
- Well, I know you're wrong.

06:15.666 --> 06:16.649
So you better think
about this very carefully,

06:16.700 --> 06:18.501
because once permission
is given,

06:18.586 --> 06:20.987
you cannot go back.

06:21.038 --> 06:22.672
Speak now,
or forever hold your peace.

06:22.756 --> 06:25.157
Fine.
He's yours.

06:25.209 --> 06:27.510
I'm sure you two
will be very happy together.

06:27.595 --> 06:30.213
Good, 'cause
when I'm done with him,

06:30.297 --> 06:34.601
Mike Ross will be begging
to be my associate.

06:34.668 --> 06:38.304
♪ See the money,
wanna stay for your meal ♪

06:38.355 --> 06:41.641
♪ get another piece of pie
for your wife ♪

06:41.692 --> 06:44.811
♪ everybody wanna know
how it feel ♪

06:44.862 --> 06:48.531
♪ everybody wanna see
what it's like ♪

06:48.616 --> 06:51.484
♪ living in a beehive
of your mind ♪

06:51.535 --> 06:54.387
♪ me and missus
so busy, busy making money ♪

06:54.388 --> 06:58.387
